<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-30-0062 </DOCNO><TEXT>The two speeches on establishing environmental standards were discussed.The discussions centered on the point of how to deal with 'unawareness'or 'partial unawareness' about relations of causes and effects in a responsiblerisk management. Ignorance alone does not legitimate regulations relatingto constitutional rights; on the other hand, however, any remaining traceof ignorance prevents the government from acting. The obligation of showingand proving of harmlessness to the environment was also talked aboutas well as the cooporation of the public in the private investigationinstances. (HSCH).</TEXT></DOC>